b'Juugo Shounen Hyouryuuki: Kaizokujima: b'The film is based on the Jules Verne novel "Adrift in the Pacific: Two Years Holiday" published in 1888. A group of youngsters find themselves adrift at sea, and after a terrible storm they are cast upon a deserted island, where they must learn to get along with each other in order to survive. \n\nOn this occasion, the human protagonists are replaced by cats.'
